entry.def: An unambitious person is not particularly interested in improving their position in life or in being successful, rich, or powerful.

example.ex: He was a reliable, unambitious officer who did as he was told.
example.tran: 他是一个可靠的无欲无求的军官，唯命是从。

entry.def: An unambitious idea or plan is not very complicated, risky, or new, and is easy to carry out successfully.

example.ex: This was not by any means a daring expedition into the outback, it was a very unambitious exploration.
example.tran: 这绝不是什么冒险深入内地的远征，只是一次平淡无奇的探险而已。
